Factor the following expression: $55z^{17}+121z^{34}$.
inference:
We can factor out a $z^{17}$ from both terms:

$$55z^{17}+121z^{34}=z^{17}(55+121z^{17})$$

Now we can factor the sum inside the parentheses:

$$55+121z^{17}=55(1+z^{34})$$

So the final factorization is:

$$55z^{17}+121z^{34}=z^{17}(55(1+z^{34}))\Rightarrow$$ 

$$\boxed{55z^{17}(1+z^{34}). \text{ Final Answer: }\boxed{55z^{17}(1+z^{34})}.}$$
